<subSubSection box="[151,906,151,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,906,151,178]" box="[151,906,151,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,906,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,906,151,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch, Bouzan &amp; Gallo" authorityName="Golovatch, Bouzan &amp; Gallo" authorityYear="2022" box="[238,784,151,178]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rotundotergum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,429,151,178]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Rotundotergum</emphasis>
Golovatch, Bouzan &amp; Gallo
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[797,906,151,177]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="98" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,885,219,244]" box="[151,885,219,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,219,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<typeStatus box="[151,204,220,244]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" box="[298,552,220,244]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rotundotergum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elevatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[298,552,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Rotundotergum elevatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[559,640,220,243]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by present designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,290,1504]" box="[151,477,290,316]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">No other component species.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,290,1504]" box="[199,1371,326,352]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,326,352]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Name</emphasis>
. To emphasize the very large and mostly regularly rounded mid-body paraterga, neutral in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,290,1504]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,361,387]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A genus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1895" box="[465,638,362,388]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chelodesmidae</taxonomicName>
that seems to be especially similar to both 
<taxonomicName authority="Schubart, 1955" authorityName="Schubart" authorityYear="1955" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Eucampesmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1320,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Eucampesmella</emphasis>
Schubart, 1955
</taxonomicName>
, with at least 12 species recognized, all in northern and northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1002,1073,398,424]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, including 
<collectingRegion box="[1201,1266,398,424]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="66300" refId="ref8497" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2021 b) Six new species of the widespread Brazilian millipede genus Eucampesmella (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zoologia, 38, e 66300. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zoologia. 38. e 66300" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bouzan 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">et al</emphasis>
. 2021b
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 2000" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2000" box="[294,641,434,460]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Atlantodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,459,434,460]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Atlantodesmus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[466,641,434,460]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="101 - 113" refId="ref9566" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (2000) Two new genera of chelodesmid millipeds from southeastern Brazil (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Myriapodologica, 6 (12), 101 - 113. [https: // archive. org / details / biostor- 201409]" type="journal article" year="2000">Hoffman, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with at least six species distributed mostly along the Atlantic coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,470,496]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, up to 
<collectingRegion box="[299,364,470,496]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Bahia</collectingRegion>
in the northeast (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, R. L." box="[560,731,470,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="101 - 113" refId="ref9566" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (2000) Two new genera of chelodesmid millipeds from southeastern Brazil (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Myriapodologica, 6 (12), 101 - 113. [https: // archive. org / details / biostor- 201409]" type="journal article" year="2000">Hoffman 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[742,958,470,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="269 - 290" refId="ref8294" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2017) Taxonomic review of the genus Atlantodesmus Hoffman, 2000 (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zootaxa, 4236 (2), 269 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4236.2.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bouzan 
<emphasis box="[835,885,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[970,1031,470,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref8357" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2019) Cladistic analysis and description of a new species of the Brazilian genus Atlantodesmus Hoffman, 2000 (Diplopoda: Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 538, 1 - 17. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2019.538" type="journal article" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
). All their species are epigean, most show vivid colour patterns, and none has been encountered in caves. All three genera compared share, among other characters, the normal pore formula (5, 7, 9, 10, 12, 13, 15–19) and ozopores borne on distinct lateral calluses; the first few postcollum metaterga slightly broader than the following ones; very broad and laterally smooth paraterga; generally smooth metaterga devoid of a distinct transverse sulcus or impression; the presence of pleurosternal carinae; long and simple legs devoid of tibial chelae; a few small ridges traceable on a depressed caudal shelf of ovoid gonopodal apertures (
<figureCitation box="[399,492,686,712]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-361@13.[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A. Incisura lateralis (I) beneath antenna, sublateral view. B. Body ring 7 with gonopods removed to show gonopod aperture, ventral view. C &amp; D. Body ring 7 with intact gonopods, ventral and lateral views, respectively. Abbreviation: I, Incisura lateralis. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669213/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
); sternal rudiments (
<figureCitation box="[729,814,686,712]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-201@14.[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A &amp; B. Both gonopods, anterior and posterior views, respectively. C-F. Right gonopod, mesal, lateral, ventrocaudal and caudal views, respectively. Abbreviations: A, acropodite; c, cannula; Cx, gonocoxa; AP, acropodital process; lo, lateral lobe; Pf, prefemoral region; PfP, prefemoral process; sl, solenomere; st, sternal rudiment; Te, telopodite. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669215/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[829,849,686,712]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">st</emphasis>
) retained between enlarged gonocoxae (sometimes extended into apicolateral lobes to subtend the robust and untwisted gonopodal telopodites), but, above all, the same basic gonopodal conformation (
<figureCitation box="[509,601,758,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-361@13.[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A. Incisura lateralis (I) beneath antenna, sublateral view. B. Body ring 7 with gonopods removed to show gonopod aperture, ventral view. C &amp; D. Body ring 7 with intact gonopods, ventral and lateral views, respectively. Abbreviation: I, Incisura lateralis. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669213/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Figs 9D</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[638,668,758,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-201@14.[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A &amp; B. Both gonopods, anterior and posterior views, respectively. C-F. Right gonopod, mesal, lateral, ventrocaudal and caudal views, respectively. Abbreviations: A, acropodite; c, cannula; Cx, gonocoxa; AP, acropodital process; lo, lateral lobe; Pf, prefemoral region; PfP, prefemoral process; sl, solenomere; st, sternal rudiment; Te, telopodite. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669215/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">10</figureCitation>
), including the typical tripartite telopodite (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1163,1192,758,784]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Te</emphasis>
), a usual, densely setose and relatively short prefemoral region (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[637,663,793,819]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Pf</emphasis>
) (relative to the acropodite); a prominent, long and fully independent, sometimes branching (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schubart" authorityYear="1955" box="[407,584,830,856]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Eucampesmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,584,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Eucampesmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) prefemoral process (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[832,876,829,855]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">PfP</emphasis>
); and a bifid acropodite (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1162,1182,829,855]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">A</emphasis>
) divided near midway into an often smaller and subspiniform solenomere (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[738,757,866,892]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">sl</emphasis>
) and a more or less enlarged and sometimes complex end or side branch (= acropodital process, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,586,901,927]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">AP</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,290,1504]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" box="[199,372,938,964]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rotundotergum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,372,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Rotundotergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[380,483,938,964]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schubart" authorityYear="1955" box="[691,868,938,964]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Eucampesmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[691,868,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Eucampesmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2000" box="[924,1089,938,964]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Atlantodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[924,1089,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Atlantodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the mostly clearly upturned paraterga (
<figureCitation box="[270,336,974,1000]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1740,1764]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,496,1717]" captionTargetId="figure-164@12.[151,1436,489,1717]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A-C. Habitus, dorsal, lateral and ventral views, respectively. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669211/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[358,389,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">vs.</emphasis>
declivous, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2000" box="[544,709,974,1000]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Atlantodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[544,709,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Atlantodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also with angular, mostly sharpened caudal corners; the presence of a weak, but traceable transverse impression on most metaterga; the distinct and brush-like limbus (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1384,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-361@13.[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A. Incisura lateralis (I) beneath antenna, sublateral view. B. Body ring 7 with gonopods removed to show gonopod aperture, ventral view. C &amp; D. Body ring 7 with intact gonopods, ventral and lateral views, respectively. Abbreviation: I, Incisura lateralis. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669213/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[1406,1436,1011,1036]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">vs.</emphasis>
smooth and even; the usual, not especially deep sulcus delimiting the gonopodal prefemoral region devoid of a cingulum distal to it (
<figureCitation box="[353,434,1082,1108]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-201@14.[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A &amp; B. Both gonopods, anterior and posterior views, respectively. C-F. Right gonopod, mesal, lateral, ventrocaudal and caudal views, respectively. Abbreviations: A, acropodite; c, cannula; Cx, gonocoxa; AP, acropodital process; lo, lateral lobe; Pf, prefemoral region; PfP, prefemoral process; sl, solenomere; st, sternal rudiment; Te, telopodite. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669215/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[454,485,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">vs.</emphasis>
strikingly deep in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bouzan et al. 2021 b)" baseAuthorityName="Bouzan" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[690,1115,1082,1109]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Eucampesmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[690,867,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Eucampesmella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[881,1106,1082,1109]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="66300" refId="ref8497" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2021 b) Six new species of the widespread Brazilian millipede genus Eucampesmella (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zoologia, 38, e 66300. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zoologia. 38. e 66300" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bouzan 
<emphasis box="[974,1029,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2021b
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
or, a little more distally, supplied with the so-called cingulum demarcating the basal region of the solenomere in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2000" box="[1105,1270,1118,1144]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Atlantodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1105,1270,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Atlantodesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="269 - 290" refId="ref8294" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2017) Taxonomic review of the genus Atlantodesmus Hoffman, 2000 (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zootaxa, 4236 (2), 269 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4236.2.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bouzan 
<emphasis box="[1380,1437,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[222,283,1154,1180]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref8357" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2019) Cladistic analysis and description of a new species of the Brazilian genus Atlantodesmus Hoffman, 2000 (Diplopoda: Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 538, 1 - 17. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2019.538" type="journal article" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
); and the prefemoral process unipartite, unciform, particularly strongly removed from, directed clearly caudomesad, and distally not attached to the acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[784,874,1190,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-361@13.[151,1436,921,1904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A. Incisura lateralis (I) beneath antenna, sublateral view. B. Body ring 7 with gonopods removed to show gonopod aperture, ventral view. C &amp; D. Body ring 7 with intact gonopods, ventral and lateral views, respectively. Abbreviation: I, Incisura lateralis. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669213" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669213/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Figs 9D</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[909,939,1190,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-201@14.[151,1436,489,1729]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Rotundotergum elevatum sp. nov., male paratype. A &amp; B. Both gonopods, anterior and posterior views, respectively. C-F. Right gonopod, mesal, lateral, ventrocaudal and caudal views, respectively. Abbreviations: A, acropodite; c, cannula; Cx, gonocoxa; AP, acropodital process; lo, lateral lobe; Pf, prefemoral region; PfP, prefemoral process; sl, solenomere; st, sternal rudiment; Te, telopodite. Photographs by K.V. Makarov, taken not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669215/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">10</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[960,991,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">vs.</emphasis>
always suberect and closely attached to the acropodite at least distally (
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[500,716,1226,1252]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="269 - 290" refId="ref8294" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2017) Taxonomic review of the genus Atlantodesmus Hoffman, 2000 (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zootaxa, 4236 (2), 269 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4236.2.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bouzan 
<emphasis box="[594,651,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[727,786,1226,1252]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref8357" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2019) Cladistic analysis and description of a new species of the Brazilian genus Atlantodesmus Hoffman, 2000 (Diplopoda: Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 538, 1 - 17. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2019.538" type="journal article" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[797,872,1226,1253]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="66300" refId="ref8497" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2021 b) Six new species of the widespread Brazilian millipede genus Eucampesmella (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zoologia, 38, e 66300. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zoologia. 38. e 66300" type="journal article" year="2021">2021b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,290,1504]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
Among both old genera compared above to 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" box="[710,883,1262,1288]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rotundotergum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[710,883,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Rotundotergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[893,1001,1262,1288]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, so far only 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1326,1262,1288]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Eucampesmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1326,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Eucampesmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been assigned to a tribe: Macrocoxodesmini Hoffman, 1990. This tribe is presently composed of only two genera, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schubart, 1947" authorityName="Schubart" authorityYear="1947" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Macrocoxodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Macrocoxodesmus</emphasis>
Schubart, 1947
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[537,714,1334,1360]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Eucampesmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[537,714,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Eucampesmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being characterized by the presence of trichosteles (= setigerous grains) on the male postfemora and tibiae, the hypertrophied valves of the vulvae, and the unusual curvature of the tracheal apodemes of female leg-pair 2 (Hoffman 1990; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouzan, R. S. &amp; Iniesta, L. F. M. &amp; Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D." box="[773,1000,1406,1433]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" pagination="66300" refId="ref8497" refString="Bouzan, R. S., Iniesta, L. F. M., Pena-Barbosa, J. P. P. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2021 b) Six new species of the widespread Brazilian millipede genus Eucampesmella (Polydesmida: Chelodesmidae). Zoologia, 38, e 66300. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zoologia. 38. e 66300" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bouzan 
<emphasis box="[865,920,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2021b
</bibRefCitation>
). Because these features fail to apply to 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Bouzan &amp; Gallo &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,324,1442,1468]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" genus="Rotundotergum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,324,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Rotundotergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[331,435,1442,1468]" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the new genus, like many other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1895" box="[911,1087,1442,1468]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="11" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chelodesmidae</taxonomicName>
, is bound to remain unassigned to a tribe yet.
</paragraph>
